cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with dialogue state tracking in task-oriented dialogue systems. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural model for dialogue state tracking. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it deals with the development of dialogue systems. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it utilizes attention mechanisms in the proposed model.
